node.text:
I sat down with Carl Ruck and Brian Muraresku to unravel the secrets of ancient Greek culture and religion and how psychedelics have altered the realities of Western culture.⁣
⁣
@Brian_Muraresku shares how and why he was drawn to research the role of psychedelics within Western civilization. Muraresku is also the author of "The Immortality Key: The Secret History of the Religion With No Name".⁣
⁣
Carl Ruck is an American professor who’s known for his work and extensive research on mythology and religion regarding the sacred role of entheogens; a selection of psychoactive plants that are known for inducing altered states of reality or consciousness.⁣
⁣
This episode was recorded on May 14th, 2021.⁣
⁣
The entire conversation is now available on YouTube, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify. Click the link in my bio to watch or listen.

node.title: Did Carl Jung Experiment With Psychedelics?

"The scientific method is developed to realize that scientists are bound to make mistakes and be human. The scientific method is to catch those mistakes."⁣
⁣
Here is another clip from my podcast with Lawrence Krauss. We discuss generated models of the beginning of our universe, the lawbreaking complexities of quantum physics, the ramifications related to entropy, the usefulness of the scientific method, and the instinctive behaviour for religious compulsion among human beings.⁣
⁣
The entire conversation can be watched or listened to via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
The episode was recorded on May 7th.

node.title: Objectivity And Reality Are Not Synonymous

"That's what philosophy, literature, I would expect your speciality - it is always those who have thought more deeply, more profoundly, and have better equipment that gives us things. That's why it's so deplorable: this petty fascism of wokeness is suffocating the number one energy of any free society."⁣
⁣
Rex Murphy and I discussed many topics such as Canadian politics, western culture, the woke culture wars, changes in universities, the crumbling study of the humanities and literature and poetry.⁣
⁣
The podcast is available on my YouTube channel, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify if you would like to watch or listen to it.⁣
⁣
The episode was recorded on April 23rd.

“There is much more we don’t know about the universe than we do. What people don’t realize though or give credit to is that there is a lot we do understand.”⁣
⁣
Delving deep into the world of quantum physics, Lawrence and I sit down to discuss a variety of topics in the mind-boggling world of quantum physics. We discuss the intricacies involving generated models of the beginning of our universe, the lawbreaking complexities of quantum physics, the ramifications related to entropy, the usefulness of the scientific method, as well as the instinctive behaviour for religious compulsion among human beings.⁣
⁣
You can now watch this conversation on YouTube by clicking the link in my bio.

node.title: The Happy Accident of Our Finite Existence.

"She didn’t like Europe, because she didn’t like the main European nationalities. I mean, the Germans and the French. She didn’t mind the Italians, but she couldn’t take the Italians seriously, but she rather liked them... She never forgave the Germans for the war, and she thought the French were sharpers, sly, cunning, and devious people. She worked in stereotypes.⁣
⁣
She rather liked the Americans, and she never forgot what the United States did in World War II, how desperate Britain’s condition was, and how overwhelmingly helpful the Americans were. She had great admiration for Roosevelt."⁣
⁣
Click the link in my bio to listen to this conversation.

I sat down with Carl Ruck and Brian Muraresku to unravel the secrets of ancient Greek culture and religion and how psychedelics have altered the realities of Western culture.⁣
⁣
@Brian_Muraresku shares how and why he was drawn to research the role of psychedelics within Western civilization. Muraresku is also the author of "The Immortality Key: The Secret History of the Religion With No Name".⁣
⁣
Carl Ruck is an American professor who’s known for his work and extensive research on mythology and religion regarding the sacred role of entheogens; a selection of psychoactive plants that are known for inducing altered states of reality or consciousness.⁣
⁣
This episode was recorded on May 14th, 2021.⁣
⁣
The entire conversation is now available on YouTube, Apple Podcasts, and Spotify. Click the link in my bio to watch or listen.

"The scientific method is developed to realize that scientists are bound to make mistakes and be human. The scientific method is to catch those mistakes."⁣
⁣
Here is another clip from my podcast with Lawrence Krauss. We discuss generated models of the beginning of our universe, the lawbreaking complexities of quantum physics, the ramifications related to entropy, the usefulness of the scientific method, and the instinctive behaviour for religious compulsion among human beings.⁣
⁣
The entire conversation can be watched or listened to via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
The episode was recorded on May 7th.

If everything is valuable, that means everything is of equal value. And as a consequence, that means nothing is of value.⁣
⁣
Recorded: April 28th.⁣
⁣
#JordanPeterson #Honesty #Truthfulness #TellTheTruth

“There is much more we don’t know about the universe than we do. What people don’t realize though or give credit to is that there is a lot we do understand.”⁣
⁣
Delving deep into the world of quantum physics, Lawrence and I sit down to discuss a variety of topics in the mind-boggling world of quantum physics. We discuss the intricacies involving generated models of the beginning of our universe, the lawbreaking complexities of quantum physics, the ramifications related to entropy, the usefulness of the scientific method, as well as the instinctive behaviour for religious compulsion among human beings.⁣
⁣
You can now watch this conversation on YouTube by clicking the link in my bio.
